==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parillin
<hw>Pa*ril"lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Shortened fr.
<ets>sarsaparillin</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A glucoside
resembling saponin, found in the root of sarsaparilla, smilax, etc., and
extracted as a bitter white crystalline substance; -- called also
<altname>smilacin</altname>, <altname>sarsaparilla saponin</altname>,
and <altname>sarsaparillin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

